n. The quality or state of being receptible;
receivableness.
n. A receptible thing.

a. Tending to recreate or refresh; recreating; giving new
vigor or animation; reinvigorating; giving relief after labor or pain;
amusing; diverting.

v. t. To greet again; to resalute; to return a salutation to;
to greet.
n. A return or exchange of salutation.

n. The state or quality of being reluctant; repugnance;
aversion of mind; unwillingness; -- often followed by an infinitive, or
by to and a noun, formerly sometimes by against.

n. The state or condition of being repugnant; opposition;
contrariety; especially, a strong instinctive antagonism; aversion;
reluctance; unwillingness, as of mind, passions, principles, qualities,
and the like.

v make one's home in a particular place or community
v live (in a certain place)
v be inherent or innate in;

a. Producing reverberation; acting by reverberation;
reverberative.
n. A reverberatory furnace.
